cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to estimate the referential properties of Japanese noun phrases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning methods to adjust the scores given by each rule, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and anaphora resolution, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
